'''Gored gored''' ({{IPA-am|ɡorəd ɡorəd|Amharic pronunciation:}}) is a raw [[beef]] dish eaten in [[Ethiopia]]. Whereas [[kitfo]] is minced beef marinated in spices and clarified butter, ''gored gored'' is cubed and left unmarinated.<ref>{{cite web |author=EthioNetworks.com |url=http://www.ethiopianrestaurant.com/dishes/gored_gored.html |title=Ethiopian Gored Gored |publisher=Ethiopianrestaurant.com |date= |accessdate=2011-12-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120729132732/http://www.ethiopianrestaurant.com/dishes/gored_gored.html |archivedate=2012-07-29 |df= }}</ref> Like kitfo, it is widely popular and considered a [[national dish]].<ref>{{cite web |author=KimHo |url=http://imonlyhereforthefood.com/2010/02/axum-ethiopian-restaurant |title=Axum Ethiopian Restaurant &#124; I'm Only Here for the Food! |publisher=Imonlyhereforthefood.com |date= |accessdate=2011-12-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100218065733/http://imonlyhereforthefood.com/2010/02/axum-ethiopian-restaurant/ |archivedate=2010-02-18 |df= }}</ref> It is often served with [[mitmita]] (a powdered seasoning mix) and awazi (a type of mustard and chilli sauce). <ref name="Planet2017">{{cite book|author=Lonely Planet|title=Lonely Planet Ethiopia & Djibouti|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=grkyDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT612|date=1 September 2017|publisher=Lonely Planet|isbn=978-1-78701-191-5|pages=612–}}</ref>

